": {"input": ["AKATHISIA:Akathisia is a side effect of Chlorpromazine, characterized by restlessness and an inability to stay still", "AKINETIC MUTISM:A condition caused by tumors in the posterior diencephalon and upper midbrain, where patients are conscious but silent and immobile", "ALBERT:", "ALCOHOL:Alcohol is a substance that can lead to dependence and withdrawal symptoms when used excessively", "ALCOHOL ABUSE:A condition involving excessive consumption of alcohol, leading to health issues such as vitamin B1 deficiency and Korsakov's syndrome", "ALCOHOL DEPENDENCE:", "ALCOHOL DEPENDENCE SYNDROME:**Alcohol Dependence Syndrome**, commonly referred to as alcoholism, is a chronic and severe condition characterized by a strong, persistent craving for alcohol. Individuals with this syndrome often experience a loss of control over their drinking, making alcohol consumption an essential and dominant part of their daily lives. This preoccupation with alcohol can lead to the neglect of important responsibilities, such as family and work obligations. As the condition progresses, individuals typically develop an increased tolerance to alcohol, requiring larger amounts to achieve the desired effects. When alcohol consumption is reduced or stopped, they may experience withdrawal symptoms, which can range from mild discomfort to severe physical and psychological distress. Alcohol Dependence Syndrome is a complex disorder that significantly impacts an individual's health, relationships, and overall quality of life.", "ALCOHOL HARMFUL USE:Alcohol harmful use refers to the consumption of alcohol in a manner that causes problems in family life, health, and social functioning", "ALCOHOL WITHDRAWAL:", "ALCOHOL WITHDRAWAL SYNDROME:A set of symptoms that occur when a person who is dependent on alcohol stops or reduces their alcohol intake. Symptoms include tremors, nausea, irritability, insomnia, and autonomic nervous system excitation.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3